contentrichtext.text: {{Italic title prefixed|3}} '''USS ''McDougal''''' may refer to one of several [[United States Navy]] ships named in honor of [[David McDougal|David Stockton McDougal]]: *{{USS|McDougal|DD-54}}, an {{sclass|O'Brien|destroyer}}, commissioned in 1914, served during World War I, decommissioned in 1922 and transferred to the United States Coast Guard until struck in 1934 *{{USS|McDougal|DD-358}}, a {{sclass|Porter|destroyer|2}}, commissioned in 1936, served during World War II and decommissioned in 1946 {{Shipindex}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Mcdougal}} [[Category:United States Navy ship names]]
